    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Enabling inverse scrolling in ubuntu]]></title>
    <link href="http://mohhasbias.github.com/blog/2014/02/16/enabling-inverse-scrolling-in-ubuntu/"/>
    <updated>2014-02-16T09:09:00+07:00</updated>
    <id>http://mohhasbias.github.com/blog/2014/02/16/enabling-inverse-scrolling-in-ubuntu</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>berikut adalah shell script untuk me-reverse scrolling pada sebuah <code>device_name</code></p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span>natural_scrolling.sh </span></figcaption>
 <div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
<span class='line-number'>10</span>
<span class='line-number'>11</span>
<span class='line-number'>12</span>
<span class='line-number'>13</span>
<span class='line-number'>14</span>
<span class='line-number'>15</span>
<span class='line-number'>16</span>
<span class='line-number'>17</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'><span class="c">#!/bin/bash</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nv">device_name</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;ETPS/2 Elantech Touchpad&quot;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nv">id</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="sb">`</span>xinput list --id-only <span class="s2">&quot;$device_name&quot;</span><span class="sb">`</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s2">&quot;Device ID: &quot;</span> <span class="nv">$id</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nv">prop</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="sb">`</span>xinput list-props 12 | grep -m 1 -i <span class="s2">&quot;scrolling distance&quot;</span> | grep -o -e <span class="s1">&#39;[[:digit:]]\+&#39;</span><span class="sb">`</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s2">&quot;Current Properti: &quot;</span> <span class="nv">$prop</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nv">new_prop</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="sb">`</span><span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="nv">$prop</span> | awk <span class="s1">&#39;{print $1, -$2, -$3&#39;</span><span class="o">}</span><span class="sb">`</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s2">&quot;New Properti: &quot;</span> <span class="nv">$new_prop</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="c"># apply new property setting</span>
</span><span class='line'>xinput <span class="nb">set</span>-prop <span class="nv">$id</span> <span class="nv">$new_prop</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>



]]></content>
