    <title type="html"><![CDATA[install ruby on Mac OS X Leopard]]></title>
    <link href="http://mohhasbias.github.com/blog/2013/01/07/install-ruby-on-mac-os-x-leopard/"/>
    <updated>2013-01-07T13:46:00+07:00</updated>
    <id>http://mohhasbias.github.com/blog/2013/01/07/install-ruby-on-mac-os-x-leopard</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<ol>
<li>install brew

<ul>
<li><a href="http://mxcl.github.com/homebrew/">install brew</a></li>
<li>install git using brew</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>


<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>brew install git</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<ol>
<li>install rvm

<ul>
<li><a href="https://rvm.io/">install rvm and ruby</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>install ruby and manage gemset using rvm

<ul>
<li>install ruby using rvm</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>


<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>rvm install ruby 1.9.3</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<pre><code>- getting list of supported rubies
</code></pre>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>rvm list known</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<pre><code>- use installed rubies
</code></pre>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>rvm use ruby1.9.3</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<pre><code>- create gemset
</code></pre>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>rvm gemset create gemset-name</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<pre><code>- use gemset
</code></pre>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>rvm gemset use gemset-name</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<pre><code>- shorthand
</code></pre>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>rvm use ruby@gemset</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>

]]></content>
  </entry>
  
